Akbank, Turkcell, Turkish Air: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-03-24T07:43:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/akbank-turkcell-turkish-air-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  fell 1,154.93, or
1.8 percent, to 63,719.64 yesterday.  Akbank TAS (AKBNK)  : The Turkish bank part-owned by
Citigroup Inc. signed an agreement with international banks to
get a $1.3 billion, one-year syndicated loan. The loan
consisting of $405.7 million and 652.2 million euros ($916.7
million) has an all-in cost of 110 basis points over benchmark
rates, Akbank said in a statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange
after the market closed yesterday. Akbank declined 40 kurus, or
5.1 percent, to 7.38 liras.  Turk Hava Yollari (THYAO)  AO: The national carrier known
as Turkish Airlines said profit last year almost halved to 286.4
million liras ($184 million), missing estimates as costs surged.
 Turkish Airlines  fell 5 kurus, or 1.1 percent, to 4.51 liras.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL TI): Turkey’s
biggest mobile phone company plans to pay 1.33 billion liras of
gross dividends, or 0.603953 lira per share from 2010 profit on
May 16, subject to approval at a shareholders’ meeting on April
21, it said in a statement to the bourse after the market closed
yesterday. Turkcell dropped 4 kurus, or 0.4 percent, to 9.42
liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
